<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,794,2007]" box="[151,984,794,819]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Total length 6.7 mm (male holotype), 6.6–6.8 mm (male paratypes, n = 5).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,794,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">
Head and thorax. Head (
<figureCitation box="[471,548,830,855]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[175,1395,312,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,301,1302]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov. 1, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 2, forewing. 3 – 8, male genitalia. 3, pygofer, lateral view. 4, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and style, dorsal view. 6, ejaculatory reservoir, aedeagus, and basal segment of anal tube, lateral view. 7, paraphyses, laterodorsal view. 8, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 = 1 mm, 2 = 2 mm, 3 – 8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/815999/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[562,591,830,855]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 29" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1653,1676]" captionTargetBox="[184,1378,948,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,916,1632]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 29. Body in dorsal view (antennae and legs not depicted). 26, Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov., male holotype (total length 6.7 mm). 27, D. sakakibara sp. nov., male holotype (t. l. 6.9 mm). 28, D. segmentalis (Signoret, 1853), male (t. l. 9.0 mm). 29, D. trinotatus (Signoret, 1853), female (t. l. 9.0 mm). The last three species belong to the trinotatus group (see text for details)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816005/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">26</figureCitation>
) moderately produced anteriorly; median length of crown approximately 1/ 2 of interocular width and 3/10 of transocular width; antennal ledges, in lateral view, with anterior margin steeply declivous, slightly concave superiorly and slightly convex inferiorly; face with frons convex, swollen, muscle impressions inconspicuous; epistomal suture incomplete; clypeus, in lateral view, slightly swollen, its profile continuing contour of lower portion of frons. Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[784,865,974,999]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[175,1395,312,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,301,1302]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov. 1, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 2, forewing. 3 – 8, male genitalia. 3, pygofer, lateral view. 4, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and style, dorsal view. 6, ejaculatory reservoir, aedeagus, and basal segment of anal tube, lateral view. 7, paraphyses, laterodorsal view. 8, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 = 1 mm, 2 = 2 mm, 3 – 8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/815999/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[882,911,974,999]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 29" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1653,1676]" captionTargetBox="[184,1378,948,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,916,1632]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 29. Body in dorsal view (antennae and legs not depicted). 26, Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov., male holotype (total length 6.7 mm). 27, D. sakakibara sp. nov., male holotype (t. l. 6.9 mm). 28, D. segmentalis (Signoret, 1853), male (t. l. 9.0 mm). 29, D. trinotatus (Signoret, 1853), female (t. l. 9.0 mm). The last three species belong to the trinotatus group (see text for details)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816005/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">26</figureCitation>
) with lateral pronotal margins approximately parallel; posterior margin slightly concave; dorsopleural carinae strongly declivous anteriorly. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1431,1010,1035]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[175,1395,312,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,301,1302]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov. 1, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 2, forewing. 3 – 8, male genitalia. 3, pygofer, lateral view. 4, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and style, dorsal view. 6, ejaculatory reservoir, aedeagus, and basal segment of anal tube, lateral view. 7, paraphyses, laterodorsal view. 8, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 = 1 mm, 2 = 2 mm, 3 – 8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/815999/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,180,1046,1071]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 29" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1653,1676]" captionTargetBox="[184,1378,948,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,916,1632]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 29. Body in dorsal view (antennae and legs not depicted). 26, Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov., male holotype (total length 6.7 mm). 27, D. sakakibara sp. nov., male holotype (t. l. 6.9 mm). 28, D. segmentalis (Signoret, 1853), male (t. l. 9.0 mm). 29, D. trinotatus (Signoret, 1853), female (t. l. 9.0 mm). The last three species belong to the trinotatus group (see text for details)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816005/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">26</figureCitation>
) mostly membranous, translucent; veins mostly distinct, except on clavus. Hind legs with meron slightly exposed; femoral setal formula 2:1:1; length of first tarsomere approximately equal to combined length of second and third tarsomeres. Other features of head and thorax as in the generic description of 
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[1128,1343,1119,1143]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977">Young (1977: 104)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,794,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">
Color (
<figureCitation box="[278,385,1154,1179]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[175,1395,312,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,301,1302]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov. 1, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 2, forewing. 3 – 8, male genitalia. 3, pygofer, lateral view. 4, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and style, dorsal view. 6, ejaculatory reservoir, aedeagus, and basal segment of anal tube, lateral view. 7, paraphyses, laterodorsal view. 8, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 = 1 mm, 2 = 2 mm, 3 – 8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/815999/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[397,429,1154,1179]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 29" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1653,1676]" captionTargetBox="[184,1378,948,1599]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,916,1632]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 29. Body in dorsal view (antennae and legs not depicted). 26, Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov., male holotype (total length 6.7 mm). 27, D. sakakibara sp. nov., male holotype (t. l. 6.9 mm). 28, D. segmentalis (Signoret, 1853), male (t. l. 9.0 mm). 29, D. trinotatus (Signoret, 1853), female (t. l. 9.0 mm). The last three species belong to the trinotatus group (see text for details)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/816005/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">26</figureCitation>
). Ground color of anterior dorsum (head, pronotum, and mesonotum) dark brown to black with yellow spots as follows: crown with eight (
<typeStatus box="[688,789,1190,1215]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">holotype</typeStatus>
) small spots, three pairs around ocelli, one pair on central portion close to posterior margin (two 
<typeStatus box="[579,686,1227,1251]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">paratypes</typeStatus>
with additional pair on anterior margin); pronotum (
<typeStatus box="[1271,1372,1226,1251]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">holotype</typeStatus>
) with four spots, pair of smaller ones on anterior third and pair of larger ones, closer to lateral margins, on median third (two 
<typeStatus box="[213,320,1299,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">paratypes</typeStatus>
without anterior pair of spots; one 
<typeStatus box="[744,841,1299,1323]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">paratype</typeStatus>
with five small spots near anterior margin and no posterior pair of spots; one 
<typeStatus box="[482,578,1335,1359]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">paratype</typeStatus>
with four small spots near anterior margin plus posterior pair of spots); mesonotum (
<typeStatus box="[297,398,1370,1395]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">holotype</typeStatus>
) with pair of smaller spots laterobasally on scutum and pair of larger spots laterobasally on scutellum (in the 
<typeStatus box="[355,465,1407,1431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">paratypes</typeStatus>
, the first pair of spots can be very small or even absent). Forewings brown to dark brown, translucent, with large vitreous area on basal half occupying much of discal and brachial cells on corium and outer area of clavus but divided diagonally by dark brown claval sulcus. Face with frons dark brown to black medially and yellow laterally; centrolateral portions of frons with alternating dark brown to black and yellow narrow transverse stripes; clypeus, much of lorum, maxillary plate, and posterior area of gena dark brown to black, anterior area of gena yellow; labrum and labium mostly yellow. Thorax laterally mostly yellow, ventrally with more extensive dark brown to black areas; legs mostly yellow. Abdomen, in ventral view, yellow, with dark brown to black marks on basal portions and central area of sternites; subgenital plates, in ventral view, brownish-yellow, apex dark brown; pygofer mostly red.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,794,2007]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="129" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">
Male genitalia. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[494,566,1730,1755]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[175,1395,312,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,301,1302]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov. 1, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 2, forewing. 3 – 8, male genitalia. 3, pygofer, lateral view. 4, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and style, dorsal view. 6, ejaculatory reservoir, aedeagus, and basal segment of anal tube, lateral view. 7, paraphyses, laterodorsal view. 8, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 = 1 mm, 2 = 2 mm, 3 – 8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/815999/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, strongly produced posteriorly; posterior margin convex; without processes; with numerous dispersed macrosetae absent only on basal fourth. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[1323,1392,1766,1791]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[175,1395,312,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,301,1302]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov. 1, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 2, forewing. 3 – 8, male genitalia. 3, pygofer, lateral view. 4, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and style, dorsal view. 6, ejaculatory reservoir, aedeagus, and basal segment of anal tube, lateral view. 7, paraphyses, laterodorsal view. 8, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 = 1 mm, 2 = 2 mm, 3 – 8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/815999/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, triangular, not extending as far posteriorly as pygofer apex; separate throughout their length; with uniseriate macrosetae along outer margin, microsetae also present. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1126,1838,1863]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[175,1395,312,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,301,1302]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov. 1, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 2, forewing. 3 – 8, male genitalia. 3, pygofer, lateral view. 4, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and style, dorsal view. 6, ejaculatory reservoir, aedeagus, and basal segment of anal tube, lateral view. 7, paraphyses, laterodorsal view. 8, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 = 1 mm, 2 = 2 mm, 3 – 8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/815999/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, Y-shaped; with median keel; not extending as far posteriorly as style apex. Style (
<figureCitation box="[986,1057,1874,1899]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[175,1395,312,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,301,1302]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov. 1, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 2, forewing. 3 – 8, male genitalia. 3, pygofer, lateral view. 4, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and style, dorsal view. 6, ejaculatory reservoir, aedeagus, and basal segment of anal tube, lateral view. 7, paraphyses, laterodorsal view. 8, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 = 1 mm, 2 = 2 mm, 3 – 8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/815999/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with apophysis elongate; without conspicuous preapical lobe; apex obliquely truncate, foot-shaped. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1348,1428,1910,1935]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[175,1395,312,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,301,1302]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov. 1, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 2, forewing. 3 – 8, male genitalia. 3, pygofer, lateral view. 4, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and style, dorsal view. 6, ejaculatory reservoir, aedeagus, and basal segment of anal tube, lateral view. 7, paraphyses, laterodorsal view. 8, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 = 1 mm, 2 = 2 mm, 3 – 8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/815999/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) symmetrical; shaft, in lateral view, with large dorsal lobe; without processes; gonoduct distinct; gonopore located apically. Paraphyses (
<figureCitation box="[397,508,1982,2007]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1323,1346]" captionTargetBox="[175,1395,312,1273]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,301,1302]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Dilobopterus nelsoni sp. nov. 1, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view (male paratype). 2, forewing. 3 – 8, male genitalia. 3, pygofer, lateral view. 4, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and style, dorsal view. 6, ejaculatory reservoir, aedeagus, and basal segment of anal tube, lateral view. 7, paraphyses, laterodorsal view. 8, paraphyses, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 = 1 mm, 2 = 2 mm, 3 – 8 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/815999/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="128">Figs. 7–8</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with stalk elongate and expanded apically; expanded portion of stalk bearing pair of processes directed anteriorly; rami conspicuously asymmetrical; left ramus with larger spine basally and smaller one medially; right ramus bifurcated basally into ventral and dorsal arms, both armed with inner spine.
</paragraph>
